				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Beasties that summon<a name="6106"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 9 03 12:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Heh it's a problem I test all the time... Mobs summon once
<br />
damaged.  60+ mobs tend to wait until 95%, but normal
<br />
summoning mobs just need to loose 1hp to start summoning.
<br />

<br />
I usually test wether or not a mob summons by single pulling
<br />
it to a safe location where I could zone with moderate ease.
<br />
If I can I try to make sure I can Mez it before I start just to
<br />
see what my fail safes are. I am lvl 64 So I have the Bard lvl
<br />
60 DA song.  That works out great for running away heh.
<br />
If the mob regens it's HP's back up it will stop summoning so
<br />
only do a small bit of damage to it.  The mobs seem to only
<br />
be able to summon once a tick or so.
<br />

<br />
When you get to lvl 63 you can get an AA called Fading
<br />
Memories(FM).  That AA has saved my but many times in a
<br />
dungeon environment where you can't easily run away.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
