				<td colspan="2"><span>Lionoo,
<br />

<br />
There are a ton of threads out there on aa point spending with bards.  You can do a check on this site, the old EQ Diva site, or the Concert Hall and find many, many arguments over how to spend them.  To save you a lot of reading though, let me sum it up.  Spend aa based on what you want to become as a bard.  Do you want to be a puller?  Take run 3, regen 3, the defensive aa's and the like.  You want to be a battle bard? Take all the offensive aa, such as combat fury and harmonius attack.  Basically, the one thing almost everyone agrees on though, is get instrument mastery and fading memories as soon as possible.  Both are awesome aa that dramatically change the power of a bard.  I know its not much, but I hope that helps a little bit.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
